Project identity:
Market Guardian / RetailGuard is an open source, local-first retail
protection system for small markets, depanneurs, grocery stores, and
local operators who need affordable evidence reconciliation, inventory
support, and privacy-aware human review.

Public model boundary:
The public-facing mathematical and agent-governance name is Neutro.
The public visual integrity module name is V.I.S Guardian.
The public auditory primitive module name is V.O.T Guardian.
Private research names, unpublished model names, and internal naming
used by SecuredMe are not part of this public project identity and must
not be introduced into public package paths, routes, UI text, public
documentation, datasets, white paper artifacts, or release material.

Safety boundary:
This project is designed to surface unresolved contradiction, ambiguity,
and review-required cases. It must not be used to make autonomous
enforcement decisions or to present machine output as a final accusation.

Third-party components:
Third-party dependencies, models, datasets, and services keep their own
licenses and terms. Integrators are responsible for validating the
licenses, model terms, camera-system obligations, and privacy duties that
apply to their deployment.
